1
00:00:01,034 --> 00:00:02,369
♪

2
00:00:02,436 --> 00:00:05,139
Narrator: After challenging
meruem to a contest

3
00:00:05,205 --> 00:00:07,107
in order to buy time,

4
00:00:07,174 --> 00:00:09,710
pouf was outside the palace
scattering scales

5
00:00:09,776 --> 00:00:13,513
on the citizens who had
not yet been hypnotized.

6
00:00:13,580 --> 00:00:15,415
Shaiapouf: I must hurry,

7
00:00:15,482 --> 00:00:19,119
or lord meruem will remember
what he should not.

8
00:00:19,186 --> 00:00:21,055
( Crowd murmuring )

9
00:00:21,121 --> 00:00:23,423
Man: We haven’t
moved forward at all.

10
00:00:23,490 --> 00:00:26,727
What the hell’s the matter?
What’s going on up there?

11
00:00:26,793 --> 00:00:29,296
Man #2: Shh!
Keep quiet, all right?

12
00:00:29,363 --> 00:00:31,031
Man #3: What are you
talking about?

13
00:00:31,098 --> 00:00:32,733
The soldiers stopped
way behind us.

14
00:00:32,799 --> 00:00:34,334
We can talk all we want.

15
00:00:34,401 --> 00:00:36,570
Man #4: I heard
all senior officers

16
00:00:36,637 --> 00:00:38,539
have collapsed
one after another,

17
00:00:38,605 --> 00:00:41,007
like puppets
whose strings have been cut.

18
00:00:42,342 --> 00:00:44,010
Man #5: There haven’t
been any warnings

19
00:00:44,077 --> 00:00:45,512
about stepping
out of line lately.

20
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:48,448
Man #6: I keep
hearing loud noises

21
00:00:48,515 --> 00:00:51,351
coming from the palace.
Something isn’t right!

22
00:00:51,418 --> 00:00:53,253
Man #1: Wait.
You think it’s a...

23
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,555
Man #2: A coup d’état?

24
00:00:56,356 --> 00:00:57,524
( Crowd gasps )

25
00:00:59,593 --> 00:01:01,095
( Crowd sighs )

26
00:01:01,161 --> 00:01:03,096
♪

27
00:01:04,565 --> 00:01:06,300
( Shaiapouf groans )

28
00:01:06,366 --> 00:01:09,436
After giving the king
6/7 of my body,

29
00:01:09,503 --> 00:01:13,507
i’m significantly weaker.
I’ve lost so much power.

30
00:01:13,574 --> 00:01:17,178
The scales aren’t scattering
as well as I would like,

31
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:20,481
and I don’t see any of pitou’s
puppets around anywhere.

32
00:01:21,715 --> 00:01:24,318
Does that mean the battle
with the boy

33
00:01:24,384 --> 00:01:27,721
is so intense that aura
cannot be spared on puppets?

34
00:01:27,788 --> 00:01:29,490
Surely not.

35
00:01:30,724 --> 00:01:32,125
Based on his appearance,

36
00:01:32,192 --> 00:01:35,128
I can’t imagine
he would be that strong.

37
00:01:35,195 --> 00:01:38,765
I cannot use my segments
while scattering my scales.

38
00:01:38,832 --> 00:01:40,667
Even so, I need to hurry

39
00:01:40,734 --> 00:01:43,337
and kill the woman
while there’s still time.

40
00:01:43,403 --> 00:01:45,405
I’ll do whatever it takes.

41
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:48,709
This is my chance.
There won’t be another!

42
00:01:49,810 --> 00:01:50,744
♪

43
00:01:50,811 --> 00:01:52,746
( Singing in Japanese )

44
00:02:34,388 --> 00:02:36,323
♪

45
00:02:39,393 --> 00:02:41,328
( Footsteps )

46
00:02:47,201 --> 00:02:49,637
Ikalgo: I need you
to go and find all four women

47
00:02:49,703 --> 00:02:51,305
and bring them back here.

48
00:02:51,371 --> 00:02:53,540
Palm: Are you telling me
that they didn’t run away?

49
00:02:53,607 --> 00:02:55,175
Ikalgo: Yeah.

50
00:02:55,242 --> 00:02:58,178
And you better tie up
their hands and blindfold them.

51
00:02:58,245 --> 00:02:59,646
I can’t let them see me.

52
00:02:59,713 --> 00:03:01,315
No time to explain.

53
00:03:01,381 --> 00:03:04,618
Palm: I understand.
That makes sense.

54
00:03:04,685 --> 00:03:08,088
By the way,
why did you bring him along?

55
00:03:11,558 --> 00:03:13,160
Welfin: Hmm? Huh?

56
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:18,398
Me, a messenger?

57
00:03:18,465 --> 00:03:20,400
Ikalgo: Go tell the king,

58
00:03:20,467 --> 00:03:23,670
or at least go find
and tell the royal guards

59
00:03:23,737 --> 00:03:26,540
that the woman’s
in the underground warehouse.

60
00:03:26,607 --> 00:03:29,376
Let them know that we’re
looking to negotiate a deal.

61
00:03:30,777 --> 00:03:33,046
Do that, and you’re free.

62
00:03:33,113 --> 00:03:35,415
( Welfin sighs )
This is probably a trap, right?

63
00:03:35,482 --> 00:03:38,151
And that’s what i’m
gonna tell the king.

64
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:41,154
Say anything else,
and he’ll get suspicious.

65
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:42,222
Ikalgo: Fine.

66
00:03:42,289 --> 00:03:43,724
( Welfin thinking ) Wait.

67
00:03:43,790 --> 00:03:46,326
The fact that i’m doing
the enemy’s bidding at all

68
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:48,762
may be enough
to anger the king.

69
00:03:48,829 --> 00:03:51,765
Ah, i’m not
about to dig my own grave.

70
00:03:55,736 --> 00:03:58,239
All right. I’ll give it a shot.

71
00:03:58,305 --> 00:04:00,374
Ikalgo: Can you drive?

72
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:02,542
( Welfin scoffs )
A lot better than you.

73
00:04:08,415 --> 00:04:11,585
Palm: It’s absolutely critical
that he carries out his mission.

74
00:04:11,652 --> 00:04:15,589
It means i’ll lose pouf,
but I should keep an eye on him.

75
00:04:15,656 --> 00:04:16,590
Ikalgo: Palm.

76
00:04:20,627 --> 00:04:21,561
It’s fine.

77
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:30,204
Welfin, once this is all over,
you’re free.

78
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,705
Welfin: Huh?

79
00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:33,674
Ikalgo: Then go find gyro.

80
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:34,674
Welfin: Huh?

81
00:04:37,678 --> 00:04:40,114
( Growls )

82
00:04:40,180 --> 00:04:43,517
Don’t press your damn luck,
or i’ll murder you!

83
00:04:43,584 --> 00:04:46,420
Don’t you dare speak his name!
What do you know?!

84
00:04:46,486 --> 00:04:49,322
Just who do you
think you are?! Huh?!

85
00:04:49,389 --> 00:04:52,325
Ikalgo: I know that, zaiqahal.

86
00:04:52,392 --> 00:04:53,460
( Welfin gasps )

87
00:04:53,527 --> 00:04:55,029
Huh?

88
00:04:55,095 --> 00:04:57,698
( Shuddering )

89
00:05:01,735 --> 00:05:03,637
How...

90
00:05:04,705 --> 00:05:08,275
How’d you know about...

91
00:05:08,342 --> 00:05:10,244
My old name?

92
00:05:11,512 --> 00:05:14,081
I never told anyone.

93
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:16,383
Ikalgo: I don’t know mine,

94
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:21,055
and I don’t expect I ever will,
but we were friends.

95
00:05:22,289 --> 00:05:24,057
Welfin: We were friends?

96
00:05:24,124 --> 00:05:25,058
Ikalgo: From before.

97
00:05:30,564 --> 00:05:32,299
( Welfin gasping )

98
00:05:32,366 --> 00:05:34,702
Ikalgo: The ants
are our enemies,

99
00:05:34,768 --> 00:05:37,604
enemies of the ngl.

100
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:42,142
Am I wrong?

101
00:05:43,243 --> 00:05:46,146
( Welfin groans )

102
00:05:47,447 --> 00:05:50,183
Ikalgo: Bloster’s
forgotten his past,

103
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:52,452
but he was one of us, too.

104
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:53,754
Take him with you.

105
00:06:04,398 --> 00:06:09,436
Welfin: Hey, ikalgo, tell me.
How do you know?

106
00:06:09,503 --> 00:06:10,537
( Ikalgo gasps )

107
00:06:10,604 --> 00:06:12,139
Wait. What do you mean?

108
00:06:12,206 --> 00:06:16,110
Welfin: You just said
you wanted me to find gyro,

109
00:06:16,176 --> 00:06:18,211
but the only reason
you’d say that

110
00:06:18,278 --> 00:06:20,147
is if you knew he was alive.

111
00:06:20,214 --> 00:06:24,151
Ikalgo: Yeah,
that’s true, but I...

112
00:06:24,218 --> 00:06:26,687
Don’t know if he’s alive.

113
00:06:26,753 --> 00:06:28,555
I just know he has to be.

114
00:06:28,622 --> 00:06:30,624
Welfin: Eh?

115
00:06:30,691 --> 00:06:33,160
Ikalgo: We "survived,"
didn’t we?

116
00:06:33,227 --> 00:06:37,565
So I know he wouldn’t
let himself get digested.

117
00:06:37,631 --> 00:06:40,467
( Welfin growls )

118
00:06:46,039 --> 00:06:47,440
( Buzzer blares )

119
00:06:54,648 --> 00:06:57,317
Damn it. Damn it.

120
00:06:58,652 --> 00:07:00,521
Damn it!

121
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:14,334
( Menthuthuyoupi groans )

122
00:07:14,401 --> 00:07:18,472
I really hope
you’re sure about this, pouf.

123
00:07:18,539 --> 00:07:20,441
It’s already been ten minutes,

124
00:07:20,507 --> 00:07:23,543
and I don’t see any sign
of pitou returning.

125
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:24,611
( Coughs )

126
00:07:29,716 --> 00:07:32,018
♪

127
00:07:39,393 --> 00:07:41,028
Welfin: Get out.

128
00:07:46,333 --> 00:07:50,204
Untie yourselves,
and use the truck to escape.

129
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:53,640
Once you’re outside,
you’ll realize what’s going on.

130
00:07:55,742 --> 00:07:57,444
( Engine starts )

131
00:08:14,561 --> 00:08:18,565
As much as I hate to admit it,
ikalgo’s right.

132
00:08:18,632 --> 00:08:22,603
Gyro wouldn’t die for nothing,
not the gyro I know.

133
00:08:25,072 --> 00:08:27,007
Fine. The ants are our enemy.

134
00:08:28,308 --> 00:08:30,944
I owe him
for giving me a wake-up call,

135
00:08:31,011 --> 00:08:33,080
so i’ll be his messenger.

136
00:08:36,717 --> 00:08:38,052
( Buzzer blares )

137
00:08:39,319 --> 00:08:40,620
Menthuthuyoupi: Huh?

138
00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:54,367
Stop!

139
00:08:54,434 --> 00:08:55,669
( Brakes squeal )

140
00:08:55,736 --> 00:08:57,271
( Welfin grunts ) Eh?

141
00:08:57,337 --> 00:08:59,506
♪

142
00:08:59,573 --> 00:09:01,975
Wait. Sir youpi?

143
00:09:03,310 --> 00:09:06,980
Look at that.
I already found a royal guard.

144
00:09:14,555 --> 00:09:17,691
Sir youpi, please,

145
00:09:17,758 --> 00:09:20,628
I need to get a message
to the king immediately.

146
00:09:20,694 --> 00:09:22,196
Menthuthuyoupi: Hmm?

147
00:09:31,972 --> 00:09:33,807
Menthuthuyoupi:
The underground warehouse?

148
00:09:33,874 --> 00:09:35,242
Welfin: Right.

149
00:09:35,309 --> 00:09:37,511
Menthuthuyoupi:
They want to make a trade?

150
00:09:37,578 --> 00:09:39,880
That woman
for all their captured allies?

151
00:09:39,947 --> 00:09:41,849
Is that what you’re telling me?

152
00:09:41,915 --> 00:09:44,885
Welfin: That’s right.
Go and tell the king at once.

153
00:09:44,952 --> 00:09:46,987
He’s gonna want
to know about it.

154
00:09:47,054 --> 00:09:49,657
Menthuthuyoupi: Got it.
You can count on me.

155
00:09:49,723 --> 00:09:53,427
I see. We’re having a contest,

156
00:09:53,493 --> 00:09:56,496
so I don’t really need
to tell the king.

157
00:09:56,563 --> 00:09:59,566
If this is the kind of thing
pouf was expecting,

158
00:09:59,633 --> 00:10:02,469
well, he’s even smarter
than I thought.

159
00:10:02,536 --> 00:10:03,470
( Coughs )

160
00:10:03,537 --> 00:10:05,973
All right. You can go.

161
00:10:06,039 --> 00:10:07,307
Welfin: Sir!

162
00:10:07,374 --> 00:10:08,742
Menthuthuyoupi: Once he’s back,

163
00:10:08,809 --> 00:10:10,944
I need to tell pouf about this.

164
00:10:12,412 --> 00:10:14,381
♪

165
00:10:14,448 --> 00:10:15,449
( Coughs )

166
00:10:15,516 --> 00:10:17,818
Still, I can’t help but wonder

167
00:10:17,885 --> 00:10:20,588
what the hell
pitou is up to right now.

168
00:10:22,656 --> 00:10:24,791
( Welfin groans )

169
00:10:24,858 --> 00:10:27,761
Chimera ants are the enemy.

170
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:36,437
Gyro’s enemy, our enemy.

171
00:10:37,504 --> 00:10:40,841
( Growls )

172
00:10:40,908 --> 00:10:42,643
Sir youpi!

173
00:10:42,709 --> 00:10:43,843
Menthuthuyoupi: Hmm?

174
00:10:43,911 --> 00:10:46,380
Welfin:
I have a question for you, sir!

175
00:10:46,446 --> 00:10:47,847
Menthuthuyoupi: What is it?

176
00:10:47,915 --> 00:10:51,485
Welfin: Do you have any memories
from your former life?!

177
00:10:51,552 --> 00:10:53,854
Old memories,
like before you changed?!

178
00:10:53,921 --> 00:10:55,322
Menthuthuyoupi: Huh?

179
00:10:55,389 --> 00:10:57,057
You’re kidding. Of course not.

180
00:10:57,124 --> 00:11:00,461
I’m youpi, the royal guard,

181
00:11:00,527 --> 00:11:02,896
and that’s all i’ve ever been!

182
00:11:02,963 --> 00:11:05,566
Don’t ask me stupid questions.

183
00:11:10,337 --> 00:11:11,638
Welfin: Sir youpi.

184
00:11:11,705 --> 00:11:14,575
Menthuthuyoupi: What?
I told you don’t--eh?

185
00:11:18,679 --> 00:11:20,314
Hmm?

186
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:23,917
Welfin: If you try to attack me,
i’ll fight back.

187
00:11:23,984 --> 00:11:26,320
I have some questions for you.

188
00:11:26,386 --> 00:11:28,688
You have five seconds to answer.

189
00:11:29,756 --> 00:11:32,325
( Menthuthuyoupi growls )

190
00:11:32,392 --> 00:11:36,329
( Welfin growls )

191
00:11:36,396 --> 00:11:39,633
Menthuthuyoupi: I wouldn’t
push my luck if I were you,

192
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:42,303
you stupid punk.

193
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:51,478
( High-pitched whine )

194
00:11:51,545 --> 00:11:53,313
Meruem: A game.

195
00:11:53,380 --> 00:11:55,315
♪

196
00:11:57,384 --> 00:11:59,319
A game.

197
00:12:06,827 --> 00:12:10,497
Something is missing.
I’m sure of it.

198
00:12:28,549 --> 00:12:30,418
( Sighs )

199
00:12:40,994 --> 00:12:43,997
( High-pitched whine )

200
00:12:45,098 --> 00:12:46,700
Yes.

201
00:12:54,908 --> 00:12:58,812
I remember.
I was playing someone.

202
00:12:58,879 --> 00:13:01,682
♪

203
00:13:01,748 --> 00:13:05,986
Someone who, try as I might,

204
00:13:06,053 --> 00:13:11,559
I have yet to defeat
even one single time.

205
00:13:15,662 --> 00:13:17,898
- ( High-pitched whine )
- ( Winces )

206
00:13:39,086 --> 00:13:40,521
( Shaiapouf groans )

207
00:13:40,587 --> 00:13:43,023
That took much longer
than I expected.

208
00:13:43,090 --> 00:13:46,026
I’m certain pitou
has returned by now.

209
00:13:46,093 --> 00:13:49,997
I hope the king
hasn’t grown impatient.

210
00:13:52,733 --> 00:13:54,602
Where’s youpi?

211
00:13:55,702 --> 00:13:58,038
Where has he run off to now?

212
00:13:58,105 --> 00:13:59,039
( Gasps )

213
00:13:59,106 --> 00:14:01,575
What in the world?

214
00:14:01,642 --> 00:14:03,344
( Gasps )

215
00:14:13,587 --> 00:14:14,955
Youpi.

216
00:14:21,528 --> 00:14:24,965
No, it can’t be.

217
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:36,777
Ikalgo: Hmm?

218
00:14:37,911 --> 00:14:41,782
Palm: All right, we’re okay now.

219
00:14:41,849 --> 00:14:44,752
Ikalgo: What do you mean? Palm?

220
00:14:48,355 --> 00:14:50,791
Shaiapouf: Sire! Lord meruem!

221
00:14:52,593 --> 00:14:54,695
Youpi has been killed, sire!

222
00:14:54,761 --> 00:14:57,497
The enemy must be far more
skilled than we ever thought.

223
00:14:58,699 --> 00:15:00,334
Meruem: Where’s pitou?

224
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,801
Shaiapouf: What?

225
00:15:02,803 --> 00:15:05,272
I don’t know.

226
00:15:05,339 --> 00:15:07,608
Meruem: In that case,

227
00:15:07,674 --> 00:15:10,744
I suppose it’s all right
for me to begin.

228
00:15:10,811 --> 00:15:13,247
Shaiapouf: Eh,
please wait, lord meruem!

229
00:15:13,313 --> 00:15:15,282
The situation has changed.

230
00:15:15,349 --> 00:15:17,685
It’s too dangerous.
The game is--

231
00:15:17,751 --> 00:15:19,686
meruem: The game is off?

232
00:15:19,753 --> 00:15:21,488
( Shaiapouf gasps )

233
00:15:21,555 --> 00:15:25,492
Meruem: Then that means
I have won.

234
00:15:25,559 --> 00:15:29,296
You will tell me
everything you know.

235
00:15:29,363 --> 00:15:31,365
( Shaiapouf gasping )

236
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:33,266
Meruem: Is that what you want?

237
00:15:34,368 --> 00:15:35,903
♪

238
00:15:35,969 --> 00:15:37,904
Ikalgo: "We’re okay now"?

239
00:15:37,971 --> 00:15:40,707
What do you mean by "okay"?

240
00:15:40,774 --> 00:15:42,776
Palm: Killua has come to believe

241
00:15:42,843 --> 00:15:46,513
that this girl here
is very special to the king.

242
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:50,284
But as for the royal guard,
they are still quite divided.

243
00:15:51,385 --> 00:15:53,320
As we know,

244
00:15:53,387 --> 00:15:57,725
pitou tried
to save and protect her,

245
00:15:57,791 --> 00:16:01,662
but pouf, on the other hand,
tried to kill her.

246
00:16:01,728 --> 00:16:03,597
Ikalgo: Hmm.

247
00:16:03,664 --> 00:16:06,367
Palm: To put it another way,

248
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:09,403
she’s a double-edged sword
for the king.

249
00:16:09,469 --> 00:16:11,404
Ikalgo: Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

250
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:13,807
That’s too hard to believe.

251
00:16:13,874 --> 00:16:17,878
The royal guard’s command would
never break down like that.

252
00:16:17,945 --> 00:16:19,413
It’s impossible!

253
00:16:19,479 --> 00:16:21,481
Palm: Is it?

254
00:16:21,548 --> 00:16:23,583
All right, but what about us?

255
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:26,019
How do you explain
our situation?

256
00:16:26,086 --> 00:16:27,788
Wouldn’t you say
that it’s impossible

257
00:16:27,855 --> 00:16:30,825
for soldier ants
to side with humans?

258
00:16:30,891 --> 00:16:31,992
( Ikalgo groans )

259
00:16:32,059 --> 00:16:33,827
Palm: Adding humans
to the gene pool

260
00:16:33,894 --> 00:16:35,429
has led to many events

261
00:16:35,495 --> 00:16:38,598
that would be impossible
for normal chimera ants,

262
00:16:38,665 --> 00:16:41,835
so then can you be
certain i’m wrong?

263
00:16:41,902 --> 00:16:44,405
( Ikalgo groans )

264
00:16:44,471 --> 00:16:46,440
Palm: I’m sorry. All i’m saying

265
00:16:46,507 --> 00:16:49,944
is that the royal guard
can be loyal to the king

266
00:16:50,010 --> 00:16:52,279
and disagree with each other.

267
00:16:52,346 --> 00:16:55,449
They aren’t
mutually exclusive, after all.

268
00:16:55,516 --> 00:16:58,486
Some of them think
they can aid the king

269
00:16:58,552 --> 00:17:00,487
by protecting the human.

270
00:17:00,554 --> 00:17:03,657
Some think they can do it
by killing her.

271
00:17:03,724 --> 00:17:06,393
Both of these reactions
make sense.

272
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:10,931
Ikalgo: I guess.
I’ll concede that point for now,

273
00:17:10,998 --> 00:17:12,766
but you said that we’re okay,

274
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:14,568
so how do you know that?

275
00:17:16,003 --> 00:17:17,605
Palm: 20 minutes have passed

276
00:17:17,671 --> 00:17:19,606
since the initial wave of en,

277
00:17:19,673 --> 00:17:21,909
and the king hasn’t killed us.

278
00:17:21,975 --> 00:17:23,944
We haven’t even been captured.

279
00:17:24,011 --> 00:17:26,413
That’s why I think we’re okay.

280
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,881
Ikalgo: Hmm.

281
00:17:27,948 --> 00:17:30,017
Yeah, I still don’t get it.

282
00:17:30,083 --> 00:17:32,419
What the hell
is going on here, palm?

283
00:17:32,486 --> 00:17:35,289
Palm: When en was first used,

284
00:17:35,355 --> 00:17:37,824
I was carrying this girl
on my back.

285
00:17:37,891 --> 00:17:41,628
If the king had noticed that,

286
00:17:41,695 --> 00:17:45,332
i’m sure he would have come
straight to me,

287
00:17:45,399 --> 00:17:48,636
but he didn’t, because she
was wrapped in my hair.

288
00:17:48,702 --> 00:17:51,705
It might be possible
he didn’t realize

289
00:17:51,772 --> 00:17:53,941
I was carrying another person.

290
00:17:54,007 --> 00:17:56,309
Make sense so far?

291
00:17:56,376 --> 00:17:59,813
Ikalgo: Hmm. I gotta admit
it sounds logical,

292
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:02,383
but I still
don’t quite see your point.

293
00:18:02,449 --> 00:18:04,551
Palm: My point is that,
if she’s covered,

294
00:18:04,618 --> 00:18:06,787
the king can’t locate her
with his en,

295
00:18:06,854 --> 00:18:08,622
she’s invisible to him.

296
00:18:08,689 --> 00:18:09,790
( Ikalgo gasps )

297
00:18:09,857 --> 00:18:11,625
Wait a minute!

298
00:18:11,692 --> 00:18:14,228
You’re saying
let knuckle and meleoron die

299
00:18:14,294 --> 00:18:15,796
rather than make an exchange?

300
00:18:15,863 --> 00:18:20,634
Palm: Of course not. We will
offer to make a trade-off,

301
00:18:20,701 --> 00:18:24,705
and then we’ll try to buy
as much time as we can.

302
00:18:24,771 --> 00:18:27,407
To accomplish that,
we must hide the girl

303
00:18:27,474 --> 00:18:30,410
in a place
where the king cannot find her.

304
00:18:30,477 --> 00:18:33,847
Ikalgo: Buy time?
How long are we talking?

305
00:18:35,716 --> 00:18:38,786
Palm: Until the king is dead.

306
00:18:49,096 --> 00:18:50,598
Ikalgo: Hold on.

307
00:18:50,664 --> 00:18:53,600
What in the world
is she talking about?

308
00:18:58,705 --> 00:19:02,776
Sure, he’ll die, someday,
but when?

309
00:19:02,843 --> 00:19:06,580
If we knew that much,
there wouldn’t be a problem.

310
00:19:06,647 --> 00:19:08,849
You still haven’t told me
why we’re okay,

311
00:19:08,916 --> 00:19:11,585
so come on! Give me something!

312
00:19:14,721 --> 00:19:16,923
Palm: The king will die soon.

313
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:19,593
He doesn’t have
very much time left.

314
00:19:19,660 --> 00:19:20,995
( Ikalgo gasps )

315
00:19:21,061 --> 00:19:22,963
♪

316
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:30,805
Palm: In just a few hours,
the king will be dead.

317
00:19:32,873 --> 00:19:34,808
( Breeze blowing )

318
00:19:34,875 --> 00:19:36,810
( Footsteps pattering )

319
00:19:41,381 --> 00:19:43,950
Palm: Let’s go deeper.

320
00:19:44,017 --> 00:19:45,585
We need to find a place

321
00:19:45,652 --> 00:19:48,788
where only you and I
will be able to find her.

322
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:02,770
There. That should do it.

323
00:20:02,836 --> 00:20:05,906
All that’s left right now
is the negotiation,

324
00:20:05,973 --> 00:20:07,942
and we’ll
have to be very careful

325
00:20:08,008 --> 00:20:10,477
not to push him over the edge.

326
00:20:10,544 --> 00:20:12,012
( Ikalgo sighs )

327
00:20:13,780 --> 00:20:16,016
Palm: I know.

328
00:20:17,684 --> 00:20:20,654
What we’re doing is ruthless.

329
00:20:20,721 --> 00:20:22,623
( Ikalgo gasps )

330
00:20:27,528 --> 00:20:30,498
Palm: We’re no different
from the ants.

331
00:20:30,564 --> 00:20:31,665
No...

332
00:20:33,133 --> 00:20:35,068
We are far worse.

333
00:20:39,373 --> 00:20:41,308
♪

334
00:20:55,389 --> 00:20:57,892
Shaiapouf: Pitou. Pitou.

335
00:20:57,958 --> 00:21:00,394
Where are you?

336
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:02,495
Pitou!

337
00:21:02,563 --> 00:21:03,497
( Gags )

338
00:21:07,601 --> 00:21:09,937
( Gasping )

339
00:21:12,606 --> 00:21:14,541
♪

340
00:21:25,552 --> 00:21:27,621
( Singing in Japanese )

